990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Basset married Robert Basset before 1075, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1076–1127":"1076–1127","–Female":"Surnud","1127":"1127","before 1075":"enne 1075","1076":"1076","about 1076":"umbes 1076","Montreuil-Au-Houlme, Ome, Normandie":"Montreuil-au-Houlme, Orne, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Europe":"Europe"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1076–1127":"1076–1127","–Female":"Kuollut","1127":"1127","before 1075":"ennen vuotta 1075","1076":"1076","about 1076":"noin 1076","Montreuil-Au-Houlme, Ome, Normandie":"Montreuil-au-Houlme, Orne, Normandie, Ranska","Europe":"Europe"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1076–1127":"1076–1127","–Female":"Décédée","1127":"1127","before 1075":"avant 1075","1076":"1076","about 1076":"environ 1076","Montreuil-Au-Houlme, Ome, Normandie":"Montreuil-au-Houlme, Orne, Normandie, France","Europe":"Europe","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Basset a épousé Robert Basset avant 1075, à Europe. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1076–1127":"1076–1127